Describe a time when someone apologized to you
- who this person is
- when it happened
- what they did
- explain how you felt about this experience

I’d like to talk about a time when my best friend apologized to me, which was quite a memorable experience.

It happened about six months ago when he was in a relationship. At that time, we used to hang out together quite often. However, I gradually started to feel uncomfortable because whenever we met, he mostly talked about his girlfriend, which made me feel a bit left out.

One day, I decided to be honest and told him that I didn’t really want to hear so much about his relationship. Unfortunately, he misunderstood me and thought I was jealous, which made me really upset. I got angry and left immediately, and after that, we didn’t talk to each other for about a month.

During that time, I ignored his messages and calls, which made the situation even worse. Then one day, he sent me a long message to apologize. He admitted that he had been insensitive and said he didn’t want to lose our friendship.

I was really touched by his sincerity, so I decided to forgive him. After that, we talked things through and understood each other better.

Overall, even though it was an unpleasant experience at first, it actually helped strengthen our friendship, and now we are closer than before.
